parts:
Aboard an interstellar survey cruiser, 240 years ahead, depict the main command center during a low-activity watch: a calm, expansive bridge with only two crew members seated far apart, monitoring long-range navigation. The room is circular with a shallow stepped floor; the hero object is a central holographic astrogation table projecting a dim, volumetric star map (no harsh beams). Include Star Trek: TNG–inspired LCARS-style consoles: pastel ribbon interfaces, rounded corner modules, matte screens with soft color blocks, and tactile side panels integrated into curved stations.
Design & materials: seamless white ceramic-composite deck with micro-speckle anti-slip finish (satin roughness), warm gray acoustic wall felt in recessed bays, handrail edges in brushed titanium, and a ceiling ring of perforated aluminum with hidden service seams. Chairs are low-profile, upholstered in charcoal woven polymer; console bezels are soft-touch elastomer with fine grain. Add a single transparent starglass viewport band high on the perimeter showing distant nebula haze.
Lighting & mood: indirect cove bounce lighting at ~3500K along floor steps and ceiling ring; cool exterior fill from the viewport at ~8000K. Broad penumbra shadows, controlled reflections on titanium, minimal bloom, clean air with barely-there volumetric haze; tone is contemplative, orderly.
Cinematography: 26mm full-frame equivalent, standing eye level, strong leading lines from the stepped floor toward the central table, deep focus for scale. GI/PBR realism with micro-surface detail, HDR highlight roll-off, low noise. Optics: clean spherical. 
Negative: crowded crew, battle damage, alarms, weapon fire, extreme bloom, dutch angle, text overlays, logos, clutter, messy cables
Aspect ratio: 21:9
